The paper deals with formal verification of multi-agent systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science. The use of modal logics for strategic ability suggests that the paper may belong to the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The focus on reasoning about strategies in multi-agent concurrent games suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Game Theory (cs.GT). The mention of model-checking algorithms suggests that the paper may belong to the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of first-order quantifications over strategies suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL).
